          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2021-03-01T17:03:14Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>American Energy Efficiency Act of 2019</b></p> <p>This bill directs the Department of Energy (DOE) to prescribe a federal energy efficiency resource standard for retail electricity and natural gas suppliers.</p> <p>Among other things, the bill establishes</p> <ul> <li>procedures and standards for evaluating, measuring, and verifying electricity and natural gas savings, including specifying the types of energy efficiency and energy conservation measures that may be counted;</li> <li>certain requirements governing retail electricity suppliers;</li> <li>other requirements governing applications for, and implementation of, delegated state administration;</li> <li>rules to govern transfers of electricity or natural gas savings between suppliers and third-party efficiency providers serving the same state and between suppliers and third-party efficiency providers serving different states;</li> <li>performance standards for retail electricity and natural gas suppliers; and </li> <li>penalties for suppliers who fail to document the adequate savings required by this bill.</li> </ul>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2019-07-25T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
        </item>
